## About the Deal
On December 3, 2025, EQB Inc. the parent company of EQ Bank, Canada's seventh-largest bank by assets announced a definitive agreement to acquire PC Financial from Loblaw Companies Limited for approximately $800 million, 
paid through a combination of cash and EQB shares.

The transaction includes President's Choice Bank, PC Financial Insurance Agency Inc., PC Financial Insurance Brokers Inc., and affiliated entities. 
Upon closing, Loblaw will hold a minimum 17% stake in EQB and receive two board seats. 
The deal is pending approval from Canada's Minister of Finance and clearance under the Competition Act, with closing expected by end of 2026.

The acquisition will expand EQB's customer base from approximately 761,000 to nearly 3.5 million, add $5.8 billion in assets, and include over two million active PC Mastercard accounts -one of the largest credit card portfolios in Canada. 
As part of the agreement, EQB will become the exclusive financial partner of the PC Optimum loyalty program, which has over 17.5 million active members nationwide. 
EQB CEO Chadwick Westlake has described the transaction as making EQB "omnichannel for the first time."


## Risk Register Overview
The Risk Register identifies and analyzes three key risks associated with the 
EQB–PC Financial acquisition:

Risk 1 – Cybersecurity Breach During Integration (High Priority)
Risk 2 – Regulatory Approval Delay (Medium Priority)**  
Risk 3 – Cross-Sell Conversion Opportunity (Positive Risk – High Priority) 
